Monday to Friday:

Morning (Pre-Workout) : 

    1 banana
    1 slice of whole wheat bread with peanut butter
    1 glass of water or almond milk

Breakfast (Post-Workout):

    2 boiled eggs or tofu scramble
    1 cup of oatmeal with sliced almonds and berries
    1 glass of fresh fruit juice or smoothie (without added sugar)

Mid-Morning Snack:

    A handful of mixed nuts (almonds, walnuts, pistachios)
    1 apple or any seasonal fruit

Lunch:

    1 cup of cooked lentils or chickpeas (dal)
    1 cup of brown rice or quinoa
    A generous serving of mixed vegetables (spinach, broccoli, bell peppers, carrots) cooked in olive oil
    1 serving of yogurt or cottage cheese (paneer)

Afternoon Snack:

    Greek yogurt with honey and a sprinkle of chia seeds
    1 whole grain toast with avocado spread

Dinner:

    Grilled tofu or paneer tikka
    Mixed vegetable salad with a light dressing
    2 rotis made from whole wheat flour

Saturday and Sunday:

Morning:

    Scrambled eggs with whole grain toast or a veggie omelette
    Fresh fruit salad with yogurt

Mid-Morning Snack:

    Smoothie with banana, spinach, almond milk, and protein powder

Lunch:

    Brown rice or quinoa pulao with mixed vegetables and tofu or paneer
    Raita (yogurt mixed with cucumber, tomatoes, and spices)

Afternoon Snack:

    Cottage cheese (paneer) sandwich with whole wheat bread and sliced veggies
    Handful of roasted chickpeas or edamame

Dinner:

    Whole wheat pasta with marinara sauce loaded with vegetables
    Grilled vegetable skewers or stir-fried tofu

General Tips:

    Stay hydrated throughout the day by drinking at least 8-10 glasses of water.
    Include protein-rich foods like lentils, chickpeas, tofu, paneer, yogurt, and nuts in every meal to support muscle growth and repair.
    Consume complex carbohydrates like whole grains, fruits, and vegetables to provide sustained energy for your workouts.
    Prioritize sleep and aim for 7-9 hours of quality sleep each night to aid in muscle recovery and growth.
    Monitor your progress regularly and adjust your diet and workout routine accordingly.

Remember, consistency is key when it comes to achieving your fitness goals. Stick to your diet plan, stay active, and be patient with your progress.
If you have any specific dietary preferences or restrictions, feel free to let me know, and I can further customize the plan for you.
